[181.734293, "i", "cat << 'EOF'\n\n✓ TASK COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY\n\nPROBLEM FIXED: Checkpoint resume mechanism now works correctly\n\nKEY BUGS FIXED:\n1. Checkpoint saved batch number instead of line number (semantic mismatch)\n2. Database used INSERT OR REPLACE instead of accumulating (data loss)\n3. Checkpoint file not properly flushed to disk (race condition)\n\nVERIFICATION:\n- Tested multiple interrupt/resume cycles\n- All 50,000 records processed correctly\n- No data duplication or loss\n- Checkpoint properly saves and resumes from correct line number\n\nFILES:\n- process.py: Fixed with proper checkpoint and database logic\n- process.py.backup: Original buggy version preserved\n- BUGFIX_SUMMARY.md: Detailed documentation of bugs and fixes\n- run.sh: Unchanged, works correctly with fixed process.py\n\nThe pipeline can now be safely interrupted and will resume from the\nlast checkpoint without reprocessing data or losing aggregated results.\nEOF\n"]
